                                    <list>
                                        <item>
                                            <p>Paper, about 7 in. by 4 7/8, consisting of 69 leaves,
                                                some of which are slightly stained and torn,
                                                especially foll. 1—3, 7, 8, 10, 41, and. 42. The
                                                quires are signed with letters from <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܕ</foreign> to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܟܐ</foreign>, and by
                                                a later hand from <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝ</foreign> to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܙ</foreign>. Consequently, the first
                                                13 are lost; and there are also lacunae after foll.
                                                1 and 9. The number of lines in each page varies
                                                from 15 to 26.</p>
                                        </item>
                                    </list>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
